A billionaire Arab prince has been charged with being drunk on an aircraft after being thrown off a passenger jet by police officers armed with 50,000 volt Taser guns.

Bahraini national Mubarak Hamad, 29, will appear before magistrates in London later this month in connection with the incident at Heathrow airport in July.

Hamad - believed to be a close relative of Bahrain’s King Hamad bin Isa Al Khalifa - lives in Eaton Square, Belgravia, one of central London’s most sought after addresses.

